Package eu.iv4xr.framework.exampleTestAgentUsage

Class GCDGame

java.lang.Object
eu.iv4xr.framework.exampleTestAgentUsage.GCDGame
public class GCDGame extends Object
A simple game as an example of "Program under Test". This class implements a game called GCD-game. The game is played on an imaginary 2D grid space. The game maintains three variebles/fields: (x,y,gcd). The fields x,y represent the current position of the player in the 2D grid. Any non-negative x,y are valid. The greatest common divisor of these x and y is stored in the field gcd. The player can move up, down, left or right, one square at at time. The player wins if he/she manage to find a square whose greatest common divisor is 1 (in other words, if x and y are relative prime to each other).
